original: Björck, Anna Ingeborg Åmalia, författarinna, Göteborg, f. 14/4/80 i Vinberg, Hall. 1., av prosten G. L. B. o. Maria v. Vicken. — Avg:ex. fr. h. lär:nesem. 02. Statsstip. 09 o. 30, res. i Norden, Tyskl., Ital., Frankr. o. Span. Lär. v. Majornas elem:lärov. f. fl. 02-37, v. Majornas komm. flick-sk. 37-45. Skr.: Trotsare o. längtare (10), Löjtnant Loke (11), Dikt o. bikt (13), Blomsterkonungen på Hammarby (22), En människas röst (28), med-arb. i Från gamla prästhem (29), Mår-backa o. Övrahd (41), htt :krit., kåserier o. resebrev i ett flert. tidn. und. sign. Enafo’SS, Gon brio, InteiMament, Tändstickan o. A. Bj. (tid. sign.: Amo, Nalam, Ingemar). GMmf, pen-ningbelön. av Sv. akad. o. De nio.
translated: Björck, Anna Ingeborg Åmalia, author, Gothenburg, born April 14, 1880 in Vinberg, Halland County, daughter of the pastor G. L. B. and Maria v. Vicken. Graduated from teacher's college in 1902. Received state scholarship in 1909 and 1930, traveled in Nordic countries, Germany, Italy, France, and Spain. Taught at Majorna elementary school from 1902 to 1937 and at Majorna municipal girls' school from 1937 to 1945. Wrote: "Trotsare o. längtare" (Defiant and Longing) (1910), "Löjtnant Loke" (Lieutenant Loke) (1911), "Dikt o. bikt" (Poetry and Confession) (1913), "Blomsterkonungen på Hammarby" (The Flower King at Hammarby) (1922), "En människas röst" (A Person's Voice) (1928), contributed to "Från gamla prästhem" (From Old Parsonages) (1929), "Mårbacka o. Övrahd" (Mårbacka and Övrahd) (1941), and wrote criticism, essays, and travelogues in several newspapers under the pen names Enafo'SS, Gon brio, InteiMament, Tändstickan, and A. Bj. (formerly signed as Amo, Nalam, and Ingemar). Received scholarship from the Swedish Academy and the Literary Nine Society. Married (date not specified).

awards.name: Scholarship from the Literary Nine Society
